  "narrative": {
    "intro": "Federal contract obligations in Nevada for FY2026 to date total $2.5B across 17,988 awards, with an average award size of $140K. Obligations fell 36.8% year over year. The state’s FY2026 to date total contrasts with a multi-year upward trend from FY21 through FY25: $3.1B in FY21, $3.3B in FY22, $3.7B in FY23, $3.9B in FY24, and $4B in FY25. The Department of Energy, Department of Defense, and General Services Administration are the largest buying agencies through the current fiscal year, together accounting for the majority of FY2026 to date obligations. Facilities Support Services, Automobile Manufacturing, and Engineering Services are the top industries by obligations in FY2026 to date. On the vendor side, a small set of firms capture a large share of spending: MISSION SUPPORT & TEST SERVICES LLC, FLEET VEHICLE SOURCE INC, and JT4 LLC together account for a substantial portion of Nevada obligations through the fiscal year to date. All figures are contract obligations; current-year totals are partial (fiscal year to date).",
    "sections": [
      {
        "heading": "How do FY2026 to date obligations compare with recent fiscal years?",
        "body": "Obligations fell 36.8% year over year. FY2026 to date obligations are $2.5B, following $4B in FY25, $3.9B in FY24, $3.7B in FY23, $3.3B in FY22, and $3.1B in FY21. The FY2026 to date total is a partial fiscal year figure."
      },
      {
        "heading": "Which agencies, vendors, and industries dominate FY2026 to date obligations?",
        "body": "The top buying agencies in FY2026 to date are Department of Energy ($966M), Department of Defense ($864M), and General Services Administration ($478M). The largest vendors in FY2026 to date are MISSION SUPPORT & TEST SERVICES LLC ($913M), FLEET VEHICLE SOURCE INC ($416M), and JT4 LLC ($259M). The leading industries by obligations in FY2026 to date are Facilities Support Services ($984M), Automobile Manufacturing ($416M), and Engineering Services ($383M)."
      }
    ]
  },
